# Customer Workspace Shell (DWS.01 port)

Reference: `DQ_PROD_DWS01-main` TransactionShell + AppChrome + AppSidebar patterns. Port visually; do not mix legacy TMaaS dashboard chrome.

## Shell layout
- Use **flex row**: `sidebar shrink-0` + `main flex-1 min-w-0`. Never `fixed sidebar` + `margin-left` on content (causes horizontal overflow).
- Desktop sidebar: `lg:static` in flex flow. Mobile sidebar: `fixed` overlay with backdrop.
- Footer belongs inside the main column, not in a separate offset wrapper.

## Brand / identity
- **Expanded sidebar**: show TMaaS logo in sidebar header only.
- **Collapsed sidebar**: show DQ mark in sidebar header only — never duplicate in top chrome on desktop.
- **Top chrome lockup** (mark + TMaaS): **mobile only** (`lg:hidden`). On desktop the sidebar always carries brand (full logo or mark).
- User identity uses **DWS.01 AvatarLockup** in SolutionChrome (deterministic initials + display name only). No organisation sub-label, no pill dropdown, no shadcn DropdownMenu in chrome.
- Sign out lives in the sidebar footer only — never duplicate an avatar card in the sidebar footer.

## Sidebar footer
- Help / Support (mailto) + Sign out only — match DWS.01 AppSidebar footer.

## Page content
- Working pages use `min-w-0` on flex children to prevent overflow.
- Main + aside: `flex flex-col xl:flex-row` with fixed aside width (`xl:w-[260px]`), not grid without `min-w-0`.
- Tables: adequate row padding (`py-3.5`), `line-clamp-2` for long titles; avoid aggressive `max-w` truncate on primary column.
- Page aside actions: **RailSection** + **RailActionCard** (icon tile, title, one-line short subtext). Use RailActionLink only for compact single-line actions without descriptions.
- **My Requests** (`/dashboard/requests`): use DWS.01 `@dbp/shell-transaction` `WorkingLayout` + `lib/dws-requests/RequestListPage` + `@dbp/ui` primitives — not custom `RequestsTable` / `RequestsToolbar`.
- `@dbp/*` packages live in `packages/*.tgz` (from DQ_PROD_DWS01-main). Next.js needs `transpilePackages`, `experimental.extensionAlias` for `.js` imports, and `next build --webpack` (Turbopack panics on @dbp/ui unicode comments).
- Customer nav sections: ORIENTATION (Overview), MARKETPLACE (Explore Services), WORKSPACE (My Requests) — no SETTINGS section in sidebar.
